  "preFix": {
    "title": "Roast beef sirloin",
    "subtitle": "Salt-rubbed, rested, and served pink",
    "excerpt": "A joint of sirloin roasted hot and fast, rested until the juices settle, and carved in thick slices. The centrepiece of a British Sunday lunch.",
    "sourceNotes": "Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136. Roast beef entries, temperatures and resting times.\n\nEliza Acton, Modern Cookery for Private Families (1845), Project Gutenberg. Roast beef method and basting guidance.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roast sirloin is the joint that earns the name. It runs along the back of the animal above the ribs: well-exercised enough to have flavour, tender enough to eat pink. A 1.5 kg boneless sirloin feeds six and cooks in just over an hour.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The two critical things are a probe thermometer and patience. Pull the joint at 52 degrees C for rare to medium-rare, then rest it for at least 30 minutes. Cut into it early and the juices run across the board.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "What you need",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "ingredientsList",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "name": "Beef sirloin",
                "unit": "g",
                "amount": 1500,
                "prepNote": "boneless, rolled and tied",
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f40e001wrkv46t35auav",
                "ingredientSlug": "beef-sirloin"
              },
              {
                "name": "Sea salt flakes",
                "unit": "tsp",
